reviewText: The DVD  lists the cars featured on the back  among them a  1970 Oldsmobile 442. There is a 1968  442 featured but if you buy it expecting to see a 1970 Cutlass you will  be disappointed. There is an Oldsmobile Birthday party  feature and if you look close you will catch about 5 seconds  of two 1970  Cutlasses but they are NOT featured on this Dvd.
We got this for my ten year old who loves classic cars. He loves the cars in this great DVD.

Great DVD. You can't go wrong with Dennis Gage, he smiles from ear to ear (if you can see a smile through that mustache) when he gets to run some of these great cars.

I bought it for the Buick's and Buick's were well shown in this DVD, buy it you will enjoy it !!!
Since I own a classic Pontiac, I found this DVD very entertaining.  Dennis Gage always does a great job.
